title: For Sale:  P-1861 MUSKETOON
postcontent:
A very nice reproduction of the Model 1861 “London Armoury” Musketoon, by Euroarms.  This .58 caliber carbine was widely used in the American Civil War and is approved by the NSSA for re-enactors.  The M1861 was a shortened version of the Model 1853 Enfield Rifle-Musket.  The British developed it as an arm for artillery crews with good accuracy and a powerful punch.  Both Union and Confederate armies favored this handy weapon, and large numbers were brought in by both sides during the conflict.  This is an accurate, hard-hitting gun suitable for hunting as well as historical re-enactments.
The barrel is 24 inches long, and the overall weight is approximately 7-1/2 pounds.  The stock is high-grade walnut with one or two very minor rack blemishes, which will easily be removed by polishing.  The lock plate bears “London Armoury” markings, as did the originals; the top of the barrel is marked for the manufacturer, Euroarms of America.  Supplied with the rifle are 119 cast “Minie” projectiles weighing 515 grains.  The proper charge for this gun is 60 grains FFg powder.  It is rifled and can be shot with the Minie bullets or patched round balls.  It uses a musket-size percussion cap; the nipple seat has been re-threaded to take a 5/16”x24TPI  nipple.  A nipple protector/safety cap cover is attached to the trigger guard by a brass chain. 
it is in near-new condition; I am selling because my eyes can no longer use the open sights effectively, but I have been able to consistently ring a 6” gong at 100 yards, even so.  The bore is bright, clean, and shiny.  Not shown in the picture is a wooden muzzle tompion, which will be included.
This rifle is legally an “antique” under the definitions in Federal law, and completely exempt from ALL provisions of the Gun Control Act of 1968. I WILL SELL ONLY THROUGH A FACE-TO-FACE SALE FOR CASH.  NO MONEY ORDERS, NO CHECKS, CASH AND CARRY.
